# DEV_README

INSTRUCTIONS STILL A WORK IN PROGRESS. 
IF YOU RUN INTO ANY PROBLEMS, PLEASE REPORT THEM ON THE GIT HUB PAGE AT: https://github.com/LBBLUG/BASTAS/issues


1. Install LAMP
   * Install Apache
   * Install MySql
   * Install Php
2. Install Git
3. Clone down the project to the directory of your choice (git clone https://github.com/LBBLUG/BASTAS)
4. Install nodejs (sudo apt-get install nodejs)
5. Install npm (sudo apt-get install npm)
6. Install nodejs-legacy (sudo apt-get install nodejs-legacy)
7. In a command window execute "npm start". This will download all project dependencies for the web site.
   * This now includes the install commands and get all dependencies downloaded.
   * This will also start a php server on port localhost:8000.
8. Navigate your browser to http://localhost:8000/install.html and run the installer.


/////////////////////////// INSTRUCTIONS END HERE FOR NOW ///////////////////////////////


9.
10. Configure MySql to have a user account for the application
11. Add MySql server account info to the config.php file, (mysql BASTAS --user=bastas --password=Passw0rd) 